Option 1: Task Manager Web App

A lightweight task management app where users can add, update, delete, and mark tasks as completed.

Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript (or a framework like React if you prefer)

Backend: Python + Flask (or FastAPI)

Database: SQLite (lightweight)

Optional: Bootstrap or Tailwind for UI styling

Core Features

Add Task: Users can enter a task title, description, and due date.

View Tasks: Display a list of tasks (with filtering: all, completed, pending).

Update Task: Mark tasks as complete or edit details.

Delete Task: Remove a task.

Optional: User authentication (login/signup).

Sample API Endpoints

GET /tasks → List all tasks

POST /tasks → Add a new task

PUT /tasks/<id> → Update a task

DELETE /tasks/<id> → Delete a task

Bonus Enhancements

Drag-and-drop task ordering

Task priority color codes

REST API version for mobile app integration

Option 2: API-based Password Generator

A small app that generates secure passwords for users via a web interface or API.

Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML + JS (optional minimal UI)

Backend: Python + Flask / FastAPI

Optional: API only, no frontend

Core Features

Password Length Selection: Users choose the length of the password.

Character Options: Include uppercase, lowercase, digits, and symbols.

Generate Password Button: Returns a randomly generated secure password.

Copy-to-Clipboard Button: For easy use.

Optional API Endpoint:

GET /generate-password?length=16&upper=true&digits=true&symbols=true
Security Considerations

Use secrets module for cryptographically secure passwords.

Rate-limit API endpoints if exposed publicly.

Bonus Enhancements

Password strength estimator

History of generated passwords (local storage for frontend)

Email password delivery (for authenticated users)

Project Recommendation for Portfolio

Task Manager App: Shows full-stack capabilities (CRUD, backend, frontend, database).

Password Generator: Quick, neat project; demonstrates secure coding and API design.
